data.07: Functional Goals - Expected outcomes of rehabilitative services

data.17: Return From Tax Payer Report (Internal Revenue Service Summary)
data.61: Individual Tax Return (Internal Revenue Service Form 1040)

data.65: Partnership Tax Return (Internal Revenue Service Form 1120)
data.67: Wage and Tax Statement (Internal Revenue Service Form W2)
data.74: Corporation Tax Return (Internal Revenue Service Form 1065)
data.76: Real Estate Settlement Statement (Housing and Urban Development Form - 1 "HUD1")
data.79: Multi-Country Textile Declaration - Statement of where different components of product were made and what processes were undergone in each country
data.80: Single Country Textile Declaration - Statement of country of growth, origin or manufacture
data.81: Negative Textile Declaration - Statement of country of growth, origin or manufacture and is used for products not subject to government textile guidelines
data.82: Endangered Species Convention on International Trade in Endangered Species (CITES)
data.85: Certificate of Ceramicware Ceramics Commodities Inspection Bureau (CCIB) - Certificate stating levels of lead and cadmium content in product
data.90: Foreign Shippers Declaration - Declaration by shipper that goods are of U.S. origin
data.92: Child Labor Certificate - Certificate stating no child labor was used in production of product
data.93: Prison Labor Certificate - Certificate stating no prison or forced labor was used in production of product
data.AC: Assay Certificate - A written statement prepared showing the properties of the product shipped, lot numbers, etc.
data.AF: Aid Form - Application for approval of commodity eligibility of certain products going to certain countries
data.AM: Ambulance Certification - Information to support necessity of ambulance trip
data.AS: Admission Summary - A brief patient summary; it lists the patient's chief complaints and the reasons for admitting the patient to the hospital
data.AW: Air Waybill - Forwarding or carrying agreement between shipper and air carrier and is obtained from the airline used to ship the goods in question; used as a receipt for cargo and contract of carriage
data.BB: Buy or Sell Exchange Contract Status Statement
data.BN: Beneficiary Certificate - Letter prepared by the documentation editor or by a forwarder stating that certain conditions, as called for in a letter of credit, have been complied with
data.CB: Chiropractic Justification - Lists the reasons chiropractic is just and appropriate treatment
data.CG: Certificate of Origin - Certified document that shows the national origin of goods, is presented to customs authorities upon their importation; in some cases, it is necessary that they be legalized by a consul of the country of destination; in some cases, they may be certified by a stateside organization such as a local chamber of commerce
data.CH: Certificate of Weight - A list itemizing the material in each package; indicates the type of package; shows the individual net, tare, and gross weights for each package; shows the batch number for each package
data.CL: Cable - Required sometimes to bank advising shipping information and details of invoice; required sometimes to be sent to customer when insurance is covered by buyer; is required usually on China shipments
data.CR: Letter of Credit - A written undertaking of a bank (issuing bank) acting at the request and on the instruction of its customer (the applicant for the credit) to make payment to, or to the order of, a third party (beneficiary), pay or accept drafts drawn by the beneficiary, or authorize another bank to effect payment or to pay, accept or negotiate drafts against stipulated documents; terms and conditions of the credit must be complied with before payment, negotiation, or acceptance can be made
data.CX: Cost/Schedule Status Report (C/SSR) - Contract status report showing budget, performance, actual, cost variance, schedule variance, budget at complete, estimate at complete, and variance at complete at specified levels of the work breakdown structure
data.CY: Contract Funds Status Report (CFSR) - Status report for funds appropriation including commitments, actual cost, forecast of billings, and estimated termination costs
data.DA: Dental Models - Cast of the teeth; they are usually taken before partial dentures or braces are placed
data.DB: Durable Medical Equipment Prescription - Prescription describing the need for durable medical equipment; it usually includes the diagnosis and possible time period the equipment will be needed
data.DE: Certificate of Quality - Certification, in the form of a letter, that product complies with the quality specifications in the letter of credit; may also state that packing is suitable for long distance travel
data.DF: DA59 Special Customs Invoice for South Africa
data.DG: Diagnostic Report - Report describing the results of lab tests x-rays or radiology films
data.DH: Nitrogen Certificate - A statement that lines were plugged with nitrogen prior to loading and a blanket of nitrogen was placed on top of product after loading to assure that the product stays dry and oxygen free
data.DI: Directory - Reports that provide information about a subject, name, product, etc
data.DL: Draft and Transmittal Letter - Written order by the drawer (exporter or principal) directing the drawee (importer) to make payment at sight or at a determinable future date
data.DN: Deviation/Nonconformance Test Results and Request for Action
data.DS: Discharge Summary - Report listing the condition of the patient upon release from the hospital; it usually lists where the patient is being released to, what medication the patient is taking and when to follow-up with the doctor
data.EB: Explanation of Benefits (Coordination of Benefits or Medicare Secondary Payor) - Summary of benefits paid on the claim
data.EX: Shippers Export Declaration - An official document submitted by a U.S. exporter whenever a shipment of merchandise goes from the U.S. to a foreign destination; joint bureau of the Census-International Trade Administration issues this form used for compiling U.S. export control laws
data.EY: Barrel for Barrel Exchange Contract Status Statement
data.F1: Cost Performance Report (CPR) Format 1 - Detailed contract status report including current reporting month values at specified levels of the work breakdown structure
data.F2: Cost Performance Report (CPR) Format 2 - Detailed contract status report at specified levels of the organization breakdown structure
data.F3: Cost Performance Report (CPR) Format 3 - Contract baseline report that summarizes changes to the contract over a given reporting period with beginning and ending values
data.F4: Cost Performance Report (CPR) Format 4 - Contract resource summary report that forecasts labor requirements for the remainder of a contract
data.F5: Cost Performance Report (CPR) Format 5 - Contract summary or detail report explaining significant cost or schedule variances
data.I2: Consular Invoice - Document required by some foreign countries; describes a shipment of goods and shows other information such as the consignor, consignee, and shipment's value; used by the country's customs officials to verify the value, quantity, and nature of the shipment, and certified by a consular official of the foreign country
data.I3: Customs Invoice - A few countries require the use of a special invoice form; usually in place of a seller's commercial invoice, this form requires all of the usual data required in a commercial invoice; if the shipment is being made to a customer, a commercial invoice will still be mailed to the customer
data.I4: Forwarder's Invoice - The invoice the forwarder receives from shipper and completes by adding ocean freight amount, vessel name, sailing date, estimated time of arrival, FOB amount, etc.
data.IA: Insurance Attachment - A sheet that states shipments made from one date are covered under an open cover policy, up to $2,500,000
data.IC: Insurance Certificate - Required when the seller provides ocean marine insurance; the certificate is a negotiable document; must be endorsed before it can be submitted to the bank
data.IM: Import License - Some national governments issue and require this document to authorize imports into their countries
data.JS: Appointment of Commissioner as Registered Agent
data.KY: Report of Assignment or Modification of Key Events
data.KZ: Request for Assignment or Modification of Key Events
data.LB: Legalized Bill of Lading - A bill of lading that must be taken to the consulate of a foreign country to be legalized
data.LG: Legalized Certificate of Origin - A certificate of origin that must be legalized by a consulate of a foreign country
data.LI: Legalized Invoice - An invoice that must be legalized by a consulate of a foreign country
data.MF: Manufacturing Specification - Instructions and or recipes to be followed in the manufacture of a product, or component of a product
data.MG: Migrant Student Records Transfer System (MSRTS) Record
data.MH: Report of Full Maintenance Period Detail
data.ML: Request for Full Maintenance Period Detail
data.MP: Request for Establishment, Modification, or Cancellation of Maintenance Period
data.MQ: Report of Establishment, Modification, or Cancellation of Maintenance Period
data.MV: Metered Volumes - The result of measurements of the gas flow through a pipe at a specific physical location
data.NC: Certificate of Quantity - Certification, in the form of a letter, that the quantity invoiced agrees with the quantity shown on the packing list; certificate of quantity may be included with the certificate of quality
data.ND: Commercial Invoice - A bill for goods from the buyer to the seller; should include basic information such as description of the goods, address of shipper and seller, delivery and payment terms, etc.; buyer needs invoice to prove ownership and to arrange payment; used by some governments to assess customs duties; serves as the basis in preparing all other documents covering the shipment
data.NL: National Insurance Crime Bureau Total Loss
data.NN: Nursing Notes - Notes kept by the nurse regarding a patient's physical and mental condition, what medication the patient is on and when it should be given
data.NO: National Insurance Crime Bureau Other than Theft
data.NT: National Insurance Crime Bureau Total Theft
data.OB: Operative Note - Step-by-step notes of exactly what takes place during an operation
data.OE: Objective Physical Examination (including vital signs) Document
data.OZ: Support Data for Claim - Medical records that would support procedures performed; tests given and necessary for a claim
data.PF: Product Specification - Specifications, generated by the supplier/manufacturer, detailing the properties or performance characteristics of a finished product
data.PG: Packaging Specification - Specifications detailing how individual products, or groups of products, are to be packaged for shipment
data.PJ: Purchasing Specification - Specifications, generated by a customer, setting acceptance limits on the properties or performance of the product being purchased; purchasing specifications may additionally supply instructions for packaging, transportation, delivery, and payments
data.QE: Quality Detail - Signifies lot by lot detail
data.QT: Quality Summary - Summarizes quality lot or lots
data.RB: Radiology Films - X-rays, videos, and other radiology diagnostic tests
data.RC: Request for Cause and Corrective Action Report
data.RR: Radiology Reports - Reports prepared by a radiologists after the films or x-rays have been reviewed
data.RT: Report of Tests and Analysis Report
data.S1: Supply and Shipment Status Report - Report contains 100 percent status on stockage and shipment
data.S2: Supply Status Report - Report contains 100 percent status on stockage
data.S3: Exception Supply Status Report - Report contains exception status on stockage
data.S4: Exception Supply and Shipment Status Report - Report contains exception status on stockage and shipment
data.S5: Product Quality Deficiency Report Category I - A report identifying a product deficiency which has the potential to cause death, injury, severely restricts combat readiness or results in a production line stoppage
data.S6: Product Quality Deficiency Report Category II - A report identifying all product deficiencies not covered by a Category I report
data.S7: "Walsh-Healey Act" Manufacturer or Regular Dealer - A report required to be rendered by a quoting party when the quote exceeds $10,000.00
data.S9: Representation - A statement (report) by a prospective contractor that makes a representation about a specific condition
data.SB: Sample Approval and Rejection List - A listing of approved and disapproved cotton bales along with a reading of tests done and reasons for rejection sent by a textile mill to a merchant
data.SC: Sanitary Certificate - Certificate of purity usually supplied by a health department
data.SD: Support Data for a Request for Quote
data.SU: Supplier's Certificate - A form that has to do with commission that is being paid to a representative because he took the order from the customer for shipper's products
data.TA: Asset Support Inquiry - An inquiry as to the abilities of an organization to support contingency or operational plans or projects
data.TB: Asset Support Advice - A response detailing the capabilities of an organization to support contingency or operational plans or projects
data.TC: Physical Inventory Request - A request for or notification of a physical inventory action
data.TK: Logistics Transfer Inquiry - An inquiry as to the current status of material transfers between inventory managers
data.TL: Logistics Transfer Advice - A response to an inquiry for the current status of material transfers between inventory managers
data.TN: Delayed Sale Report - A standard transaction to establish, reverse, or cancel a backorder
data.TP: Treatments Certificate - Form required for New Zealand and Australia that states that the container has been cleaned prior to loading shipment and certifies that no straw, rice hulls, or similar plant materials were used as packing materials
data.TR: Transmittal Letter - The section of information attached to a draft which shows the drawee and address (sold to), draft number (seller's order number), tenor, letter of credit amount, and lists the documents that the bank should get; It also shows the U.S. bank name/address to which the forwarder mails the documents indicated
data.TS: Sulfur, Olefins, and T90 Averaging Report
data.UB: Certificate of Designation of Registered Agent
data.VC: Volatile Organic Compounds (VOC) Emissions Averaging Report
data.VD: Data Request for Vendor's Specifications or Drawings.
data.WC: Request for Assignment or Deletion of Work Candidate
data.WD: Report of Assignment or Deletion of Work Candidate
data.WE: Business Conducted Prior to Qualification Form
data.WG: Appointment of Agent for Service and Consent to Act
data.ZB: Conventional Ammunition Suspension Report - An action that suspends or freezes continued use of a specified quantity of conventional ammunition
